  <wpt lat="40.165583" lon="-97.589111">
    <time>2026-05-13T11:00:00</time>
    <name>GCBMH8Y</name>
    <desc>World's Largest Covered Porch Swing Event by Harley822, Event Cache (1.0/1.5)</desc>
    <url>https://coord.info/GCBMH8Y</url>
    <urlname>World's Largest Covered Porch Swing Event</urlname>
    <sym>Geocache</sym>
    <type>Geocache|Event Cache</type>
    <groundspeak:cache id="10360045" archived="False" available="True" xmlns:groundspeak="http://www.groundspeak.com/cache/1/0/1">
      <groundspeak:name>World's Largest Covered Porch Swing Event</groundspeak:name>
      <groundspeak:placed_by>Harley822</groundspeak:placed_by>
      <groundspeak:owner id="10476383">Harley822</groundspeak:owner>
      <groundspeak:type>Event Cache</groundspeak:type>
      <groundspeak:container>Other</groundspeak:container>
      <groundspeak:attributes>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="59" inc="1">Food nearby</groundspeak:attribute>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="1">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="58" inc="1">Fuel nearby</groundspeak:attribute>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="10" inc="0">Difficult climb</groundspeak:attribute>
      </groundspeak:attributes>
      <groundspeak:difficulty>1.0</groundspeak:difficulty>
      <groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain>
      <groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country>
      <groundspeak:state>Nebraska</groundspeak:state>
      <groundspeak:short_description html="True">&lt;b&gt;13 May 2026, 11:00 - 11:30&lt;/b&gt;</groundspeak:short_description>
      <groundspeak:long_description html="True">&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Comic Sans MS,cursive;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;We are heading for Big Red and thought we would stop by and see the World&amp;#39;s Largest Covered Porch Swing. Join us swingers as we sway to and fro talking about geocaching and the Mega event in Hutchison KS. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Comic Sans MS,cursive;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;When: 11:00 am to 11:30 am&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Comic Sans MS,cursive;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;Where: World&amp;#39;s Largest Covered Porch Swing&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description>
      <groundspeak:encoded_hints>
      </groundspeak:encoded_hints>
      <groundspeak:logs>
        <groundspeak:log id="1362666801">
          <groundspeak:date>2026-05-22T18:55:37Z</groundspeak:date>
          <groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type>
          <groundspeak:finder id="12125405">gloworm77</groundspeak:finder>
          <groundspeak:text encoded="False">We are a little late for the event, but stopped to swing </groundspeak:text>
        </groundspeak:log>
        <groundspeak:log id="1360735513">
          <groundspeak:date>2026-05-13T19:06:14Z</groundspeak:date>
          <groundspeak:type>Attended</groundspeak:type>
          <groundspeak:finder id="10476383">Harley822</groundspeak:finder>
          <groundspeak:text encoded="False">In town for Woodstock in week and doing some caching before hand. We have already cached the area extensively a couple of years ago. But we are finding new things and visiting the tried and true.    
    
On absolutely beautiful sunny day with deep ocean blue skies we headed north today. Because of some error in the time loop continuim ancestral wearing a sock on the wrong foot, we had to skip a couple of caches this morning to make the events on time. Coranodo Heights E.C. and Rock City EC are great and get a fav each. Pictures do not do these places justice. Magnificently beautiful cannot describe them.

From there we hit the first event and yes that swing is long. And wonderful park with mature trees and a lush lawn.

While there we grabbed a cache just down the road and it gets a fav. 

After eating lunch in the park we headed out for Hamburg Park.

All caches were stamped with the Lab Seal of Approval unless we did not find them then they weren't but if we did find them then they were...unless they were earth caches or virtuals then they weren't as those don't have logs... well some earth caches do have logs but not the ones you sign. 

Answers for virts and E.C.s were sent by Kellygirl15.</groundspeak:text>
        </groundspeak:log>
        <groundspeak:log id="1360730633">
          <groundspeak:date>2026-05-13T17:30:46Z</groundspeak:date>
          <groundspeak:type>Attended</groundspeak:type>
          <groundspeak:finder id="12865961">Kellygirl15</groundspeak:finder>
          <groundspeak:text encoded="False">Great place for an event - thanks so much!</groundspeak:text>
        </groundspeak:log>
        <groundspeak:log id="1352762215">
          <groundspeak:date>2026-04-04T03:23:29Z</groundspeak:date>
          <groundspeak:type>Publish Listing</groundspeak:type>
          <groundspeak:finder id="531429">Heartland Cacher</groundspeak:finder>
          <groundspeak:text encoded="False">Published</groundspeak:text>
        </groundspeak:log>
      </groundspeak:logs>
    </groundspeak:cache>
  </wpt>
